Dear Arman,

We are happy to announce that your application to the 2015 =
Software-Development Summer School for Computational Chemistry, =
Biomolecular Simulation, and Materials Modeling has been accepted!

The next step is to secure your place in the program by going to this =
webpage to formally register. http://www.cpe.vt.edu/reg/sss/ =
<http://www.cpe.vt.edu/reg/sss/>=20
The registration page mentions credit cards, so I want to remind you =
that there is no charge for participating in the Summer School. Clicking =
register will bring you to a page showing a total of $0.00 for =
registration. =20

When you have made your travel arrangements I ask that you please send =
me an email (amjames2@vt.edu <mailto:amjames2@vt.edu>).
If you will be flying I will need to know the flight number, airline and =
the scheduled arrival/departure time of your arriving and departing =
flights.  We will use this information to arrange transportation to and =
from Roanoke airport.=20

If you are driving to campus I will need to get you a temporary parking =
permit, and give you instructions on where you can park. *(parking =
services has not gotten back to me yet about this).

If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact me. Looking =
forward to meeting you in June!

Sincerely,
Andrew M. James
Summer School Coordinator


